nodes.title: Auto Prompt
widgets_values: A detailed digital painting of a female knight with long, flowing red hair, wearing ornate silver and gold armor with a purple cape. She has a serious expression and is holding a sword in her right hand. The background is a dark, smoky gradient. The art style is realistic with a focus on texture and detail. The knight is positioned in the center of the image, facing the viewer.

nodes.title: Auto Prompt
widgets_values: A 3D rendering of a cute, cartoon penguin standing on a solid light blue background. The penguin has a black and white body with a yellow beak and feet, and a small tuft of black hair on its head. It has a friendly expression and is looking directly at the viewer. The lighting is soft and even, casting gentle shadows on the penguin's body. The background is simple and minimalistic, with no other objects or decorations in sight. The image is high quality and has a playful, whimsical feel.

nodes.title: VACE Long video solution
widgets_values: Here I replace images using the same first frame. But you can also use this solution to replace a set of theme series images, such as several key frames, and let VACE process them to generate a long video made up of a series of videos connected by the first and last frames.

nodes.title: About VACE Start To End Frame Node
widgets_values:
when no control_images, num_frames is the length of the start-to-end frame, which is useful for controlling the transition time. It can be different to be the project video length, which can achieve more controllable results than other flf2v methods.

control_images can control how the start-to-end frame transforms, using depth | lineart | pose etc.

use inpaint_mask with inpaint control video.

start | end frame, control images, and inpaint masks all can be generated from original video.

Control Video for:
 t2v depth lora control
 t2v|i2v fun control (multi types)
 fantasy portrait face video

nodes.title: Triton
widgets_values:
Wan Video Torch Compile Settings is disconnected by default and will not take effect if you're using fp8 e4m3 diffusion model and your graphic card is 20xx or 30xx.

If you choose fp32/bf16/fp16/fp8 e5m2 model, then you can:
1. Link Wan Video Torch Compile Settings to the Wan Video Model Loader to speed up about 15%~25%..
2. Follow the VRAM settings instruction in the Wan Video Wrapper Tips Group.

choose sparse sage attention:
select sageatten in the Model Loder and bypass the Set Radial Attention.
choose radial sage attention:
select radial_sage_attention in the Model Loder and select sageatten in the Set Radial Attention.

The speed of Radial SageAttn is faster than the Sparse SageAttn.

Wan Video Torch Compile Settings is disconnected by default and will not take effect if you're using fp8 e4m3 diffusion model and your graphic card is 20xx or 30xx.

If you choose fp32/bf16/fp16/fp8 e5m2 model, then you can:
1. Link Wan Video Torch Compile Settings to the Wan Video Model Loader to speed up about 15%~25%..
2. Follow the VRAM settings instruction in the Wan Video Wrapper Tips Group.

choose sparse sage attention:
select sageatten in the Model Loder and bypass the Set Radial Attention.
choose radial sage attention:
select radial_sage_attention in the Model Loder and select sageatten in the Set Radial Attention.

The speed of Radial SageAttn is faster than the Sparse SageAttn.

Bypass KJ TeaCache and SLG nodes when using speed up lora.

nodes.title: lora
widgets_values:
14B speedup lora doesn't support 1.3B main model

merge_loras off:
Same result for using WanVideo Set LoRAs Node or linking directly to lora slot of WanVideo Model Loder.

merge_loras on:
is only for linking directly to the lora slot of the WanVideo Model Loader and achieves a different (maybe better) result from merge_loras off.

Tune lora and lora str:
Use WanVideo Set LoRAs Node and turn off merge_loras without loading main model repeatly.

Fixed lora and test merge_loras on:
link directly to lora slot of WanVideo Model Loder and turn on merge_loras.

widgets_values:
1. Switch_at_Step = end_step splt in the graph

2. Link Basic Scheduler for Native Switch at Step. Note sigmas are approximate values.

3. You can link WanVideo Sigma To Step to end_step of 1st pass and start_step of 2nd pass Wrapper Sampler directly and do not need to caculate the switch_at_step value.

4. Native Sigmas supports denoise <1.0. Wrapper denoise uses different approach.
enable fun_or_fl2v_model for wan2.2 i2v model
